e tabletop. This foot and lower leg are covered in a light tan or beige sock, with the trouser leg pulled up to expose the sock ending much lower, around the lower calf or just above the ankle. Several hands gather near the top edge of the sock, pinching and smoothing the cuff to show where it stops. The black over-the-calf sock remains nearby in the background, creating a direct side-by-side contrast between the taller dark sock and the shorter tan sock. The men’s hands point repeatedly at the ankle area and the cuff line, emphasizing the shorter length.\n\nOne of the men in a dark suit, with neatly combed reddish hair, is shown in close-up resting his fingers against his mouth in a thinking pose. He looks off to the side, then downward, appearing to consider the argument. The focus returns to the feet on the table. A dark burgundy socked foot slides in from the right, placed alongside the other socked feet. Hands smooth and hold the burgundy sock near the ankle and cuff, presenting it as another option. The burgundy sock has a dressy, polished look, and the men handle it carefully, as if drawing attention to its styling. Papers or white fabric briefly slide beneath or near the feet as the comparison becomes crowded and busy.\n\nThe man with black horn-rimmed glasses, wearing a dark suit and tie, now appears in close-up. He faces another man whose back is partly visible in the foreground. The bespectacled man speaks with a concentrated, almost lecturing expression, his eyebrows raised behind the thick frames. He leans forward and continues, mouth opening and closing through several emphatic expressions, as though laying out his own position in the debate.\n\nThe tan-suited man reappears from a low viewpoint among the feet and legs. A dark socked foot crosses high in the foreground, while the tan-suited man looks down and gestures toward the lower legs around him. The composition makes the socks loom large, with the men’s faces and pointing hands peering in from abo